<span class="txt18">Dear Cleora Public School Parents and Patrons:<br><br>
        This week marked the start of a new and unexpected experience for Oklahoma students, teachers and school staff. While we did not anticipate ending the year with this approach, I am proud of the Continuous Distance Learning Plan that Cleora has developed to allow students to learn from home. We know this change will be challenging, and there is sadness about missing or delaying special events and activities. During this time, students and their families can count on Cleora School to support them, both academically and emotionally.<br><br>
        The next five weeks will unveil a temporary new normal for each of us. Dining room tables will double as classroom/office spaces, and our life will be limited to the walls of our own homes. I would like to thank our parents for collaborating with our district on this unprecedented voyage. While the parents will be assisting their children in person, I want them to know they will not be alone, we are all in this together. Our teachers and staff will be just a phone call, email or videoconference away. <br><br>
        Although this health crisis has created many trials and obstacles, it has also given us opportunities to help one another. In one week alone, our child nutrition team served 720 meals to local children. This Child Nutrition team effort has been supported by several school staff, parents, and community members volunteering their time to ensure its success. We were also able to donate numerous boxes of cleaning supplies to our area EMS Ambulance station and a local Medical Clinic. Additionally, our administration and staff completed the enormous task of creating a Continuous Distance Learning Plan in just a matter of days. On behalf of the board and our community, I commend and thank all school employees and volunteers for their hard work and commitment. Cleora Public School has an astonishing team.<br><br>
        We are blessed to serve a community that treasures public education and understands that flexibility and support is vital to meet the needs of students. Our school is not just a building; it is a family of caring, knowledgeable professionals making a difference for students every day regardless of the situation. Our district is home to the best, "Where Learning Is<span class="ital"> #</span>1" and I know we will finish the school year strong.<br><br>
Thank you for your support of Cleora Public School.<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Billy JarvisPresident, Cleora School Board of Education<br><br></span>
